   intmod_zero.saw:13:1-13:61 (at top level)
Error translating: Refusing to translate primitive toIntMod.

Reason: IntMod modulus 0 is rejected: SAW has no coherent Z 0 semantics (concrete evaluation crashes with mod-by-zero; symbolic backends disagree), so the backend refuses to assign Lean semantics to it.

This is a deliberate translator-level rejection — the Lean backend doesn't have a sound
transposition for this primitive yet. If your Cryptol code specialised down to it,
you've hit one of the open cases tracked in the long-term plan.

Workaround: refactor to avoid the primitive (e.g. recursion via `fix` can sometimes
be expressed as a bounded fold instead). Run dump_lean_residual_primitives on your
term to see all surviving names — toIntMod will be one of them.

